<subSubSection pageId="76" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="76.[151,1436,1591,1760]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
The classification of these two species is doubtful because of the following characters: left paramere small, widened at base and ending in a “finger-like projection” or a “needlelike point”, “all femorae swollen” and the ostiolar peritreme “short, abruptly curved backward at apical third”. The left paramere is similar to that of species in the new genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carpintero" authorityYear="2014" box="[347,434,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" genus="Anaelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[347,434,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Anaelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the ostiolar peritreme is different.
</paragraph>
